# Society Structure — Committees and Contact Us

## Overview
This covers how a society's leadership/organisational structure (president, secretary, treasurer, etc.) is recorded and how residents can look it up, alongside the society's general contact information.

---

## Society Committees (Admin-Configured)

- `SUAdmin` edits the society's committees from the Society settings page (`PUT /api/societies/{id}`, `committees` field).
- Each committee has a name (e.g., "Managing Committee", "Sports Committee") and a list of members; each member is an **existing registered user** picked from a searchable dropdown (not free-text email) plus a free-text role title (e.g., "President", "Secretary", "Treasurer/Cashier").
- **One committee role per user, society-wide:** a user already assigned to a role on any committee cannot be assigned to another — the dropdown pre-filters already-assigned users client-side, and the backend independently rejects any submission that would assign the same `userId` to more than one committee role (error code `USER_ALREADY_ON_COMMITTEE`).
- A committee member must already be a registered user of the society (resolved by email); the backend rejects an unrecognised email with a validation error.
- Available on both web (Society settings page) and mobile (dedicated "Society Committee" screen, `SUAdmin`/HQ roles only).

---

## Contact Us (Read-Only, All Roles)

- A read-only "Contact Us" page shows the society's contact email/phone ("Society Office") and the full committee list with each member's name and role title.
- No edit controls — editing committees/contact info stays on the admin-only Society settings page.
- Reuses the existing society details query (`GET /api/societies/{id}`); no dedicated backend endpoint.
- Reachable from navigation for **every role** (SUAdmin, SUUser, SUSecurity, HQAdmin, HQUser) on both web (`/contact-us` route) and mobile ("Contact Us" drawer entry).

---

## Acceptance Criteria
- A user can hold at most one committee role across all committees in a society.
- Committee member selection is a dropdown of existing users, not free-text.
- Contact Us is visible to every role and has no edit affordances.
- Contact Us and Society Committee data always match what `SUAdmin` last saved in Society settings.
